    <h1>Mathematical Induction</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Craig DeLancey &middot; A Concise Introduction to Logic, Ch. 9 &middot; <a href="https://milneopentextbooks.org/a-concise-introduction-to-logic/">CC BY-SA 4.0</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Mathematical induction</strong> proves a property holds for all natural numbers. Prove the base case (n = 0). Then prove that if it holds for n, it holds for n + 1. The chain of implications covers every number.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Domino chain -->
